      "Description": "The image is not centered, or is skewed on the page. The defect occurs when the paper is not positioned properly as it is pulled from the tray and moves through the paper path.",
      "Possible solutions": "1. Reprint the document. 2. Remove the paper and then reload the tray. Makesure that all the paper edges are even on all sides. 3. Makesure that the top of the paper stack is below the tray-full indicator. Donot overfill the tray. 4. Makesure that the paper guides are adjusted to the correct size for the paper. Donot adjust the paper guides tightly against the paper stack. Adjust them to the indentations or markings in the tray. 5. If the issue persists, go to support.hp.com."
    }
  ],
